-- PRESS DIGEST - China - Sept 19 
-- By Chen Yixin and Adam Jourdan
-- Thu Sep 18, 2014 08:55PM EDT
-- None



SHANGHAI, Sept 19 (Reuters) - Chinese newspapers available in Beijing and Shanghai carried the following stories on Friday. Reuters has not checked the stories and does not vouch for their accuracy.

CHINA SECURITIES JOURNAL - The China Financial Futures Exchange will start a trading trial of 10-year and 3-year Chinese government bond futures on Friday, the official paper said citing sources. - Amid wider reforms of China's state-owned companies, Wuhan Iron And Steel Co Ltd <600005.SS> said it is studying the possibility of mixed ownership.   SHANGHAI SECURITIES NEWS  - China's insurance regulator has sought feedback from local insurers over allowing them to issue preference shares, the paper said, citing "authoritative" channels. The regulator, which is looking to widen funding sources for the sector, is looking for feedback before Sept. 24.   CHINA DAILY  - The much-hyped Shanghai free-trade zone (FTZ) saw 740 billion yuan ($120.5 billion) worth of sales in the first half of 2014, the official paper said. Housing prices around the zone have also risen 20 percent against a year earlier. SHANGHAI DAILY  - Chinese authorities have sentenced a man to five years in prison for running an illegal money lending firm, a district court in Shanghai said on Thursday. The lender collected 26 million yuan ($4.23 million) worth of deposits from the public.